Syntax: continue <argument>

arguments: 
   <no argument> -- Will make a spell or prayer become of indefinite duration
in its chant.  Not every spell or prayer will respond to this command.

   # -- specify a number to have a prayer or spell go an addition
number of rounds.  Example: "continue 6" would make the spell go 
another 6 rounds.

   finish/stop -- This will make an indefinite length spell/prayer start to
wrap up.  It will become a spell/prayer with at least the number of casting
rounds the spell or prayer started with. Example: "continue finish" will make
a spell wrap up.

** Note, that you can always just stop to abort a spell.

See Also: - STOP
Related Topics: UTILITY
